The paper deals with optimization problems in graphs, specifically the Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP) and its variations. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms and heuristics for solving these problems, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of exponential neighbourhoods is a technique often used in Combinatorial Optimization (cs.CC) and Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the problems and their special cases, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG).
